The paper deals with coalition formation games, which are a subfield of game theory. The focus is on the existence of stable partitions, which is a concept related to stability in cooperative games. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses preference restrictions, which are a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of stability concepts and the analysis of natural subclasses suggest that the paper may also fit into the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
